<Author>jtelfer
<Content>Hotel Metropol was certainly adequate! Hotel Metropol is not for honeymooners. The walls are paper thin but the accommodations are just fine. It is certainly a good bang for the buck. The hotel lobby is lovely, offering a lot of local marble and artwork. There are two elevators that service the 160 rooms, but they are TINY. Three of us with a suitcase each was too much!The rooms provided us with a king size bed, a beautifully large bathroom (GREAT WATER PRESSURE) and good lighting. There was NO airconditioning, and that was a little disturbing considering it was in the high 80's during the day and the high 70's at night.The restaurant was good, but not great. The food was simple, but they tried to make it elegant. The prices weren't bad, but the quality wasn't great. The breakfast buffet was a nice treat, (included with our room fee). The coffee was some of the best I've ever had in my life, and as a traveler through much of South and Central America, I know my coffee!!!!The staff was incredible. Very nice, they spoke a good broken english, and were always willing to smile and giggle! The hotel isn't on a great street, but one block up, one block down, you're in the heart of it all. 
